Thus far, it is clear that there is no perfect teaching method. Some methods appear to work better depending the the course content. Yet, simply applying a singular teaching method as is does not appear to be fully effective. As a result, through the studying of different teaching methods, individuals have created enhancement methods to improve students learning in mathematics. Some of these methods include active learning, SOMETHING, SOMETHING.
\section{Improving the Teaching of Mathematics}
Thus far, it is clear that there is no perfect teaching method. Some methods appear to work better depending the the course content. Yet, simply applying a singular teaching method as is does not appear to be fully effective. As a result, through the studying of different teaching methods, individuals have created enhancement methods to improve students learning in mathematics. Some of these methods include active learning, enhancement method 2, enhancement method 3.

\subsection{Active Learning}
Active learning takes a different approach to instruction. It forces students to fully engage with the course material and their classmates. The professor is still crucial for guiding the students, but active learning places more responsibility on the students. This method is not meant to replace lectures, but to integrate tasks during a lecture to increase engagement and lead to deeper learning \cite{Active_learning}. In an analysis course students could be asked to work together to solve a harder proof or in a calculus class a difficult integral that requires multiple solving techniques. Most classes at MUN are strictly lecture based, changing that would be difficult. However, as we discussed, lecture based courses do not always allow for deep learning of a subject, it would seem that adding active learning could increase understanding at MUN as it has in other places \cite{Freeman}.

