\subsection{Personal Insight}
Based on everything discussed I believe effective learning starts with engagement. The majority of courses students will encounter are lecture based. A structure that has students taking notes, with little to no contribution. For some individuals, this may be beneficial, however, in reality, for many it is not. A very crucial aspect in instruction is engagement from the professor. Many learning techniques discuss student engagement and the impact that has. The best way to promote engagement is for the professor to initiate it themselves. When a professor is engaging it creates a welcoming environment, something that can allow students to feel comfortable to ask questions and discuss topics with classmates. When a professor shows enthusiasm it can increase students motivation to learn the topic. Ultimately, every method of instruction has its benefits.  Strictly following one teaching method is not the most effective way. Based on my analysis, effective teaching is when professors use a combination of teaching methods to create the best possible learning environment for students, while trying to increase their engagement.
